<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Carson Gross on jverkamp.com</title><link>https://blog.jverkamp.com/reviews/authors/carson-gross/</link><description>Recent content in Carson Gross on jverkamp.com</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 27 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://blog.jverkamp.com/reviews/authors/carson-gross/atom.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Hypermedia Systems</title><link>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2024/01/27/hypermedia-systems/</link><pubDate>Sat, 27 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2024/01/27/hypermedia-systems/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;HTMX. HTML, but better*!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-html" data-lang="html"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;button&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;hx-delete&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/contacts/{{ contact.id }}&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;hx-push-url&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;true&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;hx-confirm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Are you sure you want to delete this contact?&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;hx-target&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;body&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Delete Contact
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;lt;/&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;button&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Basically, the entire idea is that you don&amp;rsquo;t need quite so much (explicit) JavaScript everywhere. It should be possible to declaratively design pages that can automatically take actions (including HTTP verbs other than &lt;code&gt;GET&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;POST&lt;/code&gt;) and replace (partial) content on pages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That&amp;rsquo;s why I read the book.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>